\begin_layout Section
Problem 2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{ex}
\backslash
label{ex}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Consider the eigenvalue problem 
\begin_inset Formula $A\boldsymbol{v}=\lambda\boldsymbol{v}$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(\widehat{\lambda},\widehat{\boldsymbol{v}})$
\end_inset

 be a computed eigenpair, which is assumed to be the exact eigenpair of
 a perturbed matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\delta A$
\end_inset

.
 Show that the minimum 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell_{2}$
\end_inset

-norm of all such 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta A$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\|A\widehat{\boldsymbol{v}}-\widehat{\lambda}\widehat{\boldsymbol{v}}\|}{\|\widehat{\boldsymbol{v}}\|},
\]

\end_inset

and find a particular 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta A$
\end_inset

 whose 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell_{2}$
\end_inset

-norm is the minimum.
 (Note that this result can help us experimentally determine if an eigenvalue
 algorithm is backward stable).
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{ex}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

